# Makefile First

The root `Makefile` is the single source of truth for all quality gates, builds, and deployments. Never improvise shell commands for operations that have a Makefile target.

## Validation (run from worktree root)

- `make validate` — all linters + type checking
- `make test` — backend + frontend unit tests with coverage
- `make test-integration` — integration tests
- `make pre-commit` — pre-commit hooks on all files

## Deployment

- `make e2e-azure-route-refresh` — rebuild + helm upgrade into existing e2e namespace
- `make e2e-azure-route` — full create from scratch
- `make e2e-azure-route-down` — teardown
- `make prod-up` / `make prod-down` — production namespace

## Why This Matters

Makefile targets handle secrets loading, archive creation (via `.dockerignore`), Helm value plumbing (`AOAI_DEPLOYMENT`, probe tokens, etc.), and retry logic. Manually replicating these steps leads to missing values, corrupted archives, or stuck Helm releases.

If a `make` target fails with a transient error (e.g. `FetchSourceFailed`), **retry the same target** rather than improvising a workaround.

## Discovery

Run `make help` to list all available targets with descriptions.
